The paper deals with blind image quality assessment using deep learning, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a probabilistic representation of image quality, which is a statistical approach that can be categorized under machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a more robust loss function, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the convergence of deep model training, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
